<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-64-0827 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author discusses why the Reagan administration is reluctant to accepta U.S.-Soviet freeze on nuclear weapons. The administration claims theexisting balance of forces is unfavorable to the U.S. and could actuallyworsen under a freeze. Freeze campaigners argue the existence of a roughbalance or parity in U.S. and Soviet nuclear forces. The author discussesthree problems that plague efforts to assess the impact of the U.S.-Sovietstrategic balance on broader issues of U.S. nuclear weapons and armscontrol.</TEXT></DOC>